sections.Acquis d’apprentissage spécifiques:
By the end of the graduation work, students will be able to:
Activity 1 : MT5X Master thesis in health engineering
- formalize the engineering problem based on the medical/clinical context;
- produce a state-of-the-art;
- propose an appropriate methodology to deal with the problem;
- design a solution that meets to the problem;
- justify the choices made to resolve the problem;
- criticize the results obtained in relation to the expected objectives, by mobilizing the relevant theoretical frameworks;
- collect data to validate the solution;
- synthesize by formulating scientific or technical conclusions;
- communicate effectively in writing and orally while adapting to the target audience;
- manage the work autonomously and proactively.
Activity 2 : MT5C-B1-2020 Education support seminars
- carry out a reflective analysis of their own student path in terms of skills developed, identification of their own strengths and weaknesses, their wishes for future continuing education, with a view to their integration into the professional world of the health sector.

sections.Description du contenu:
The graduation work allows the student to actively participate in an industrial project in the health care sector in collaboration with a company or a research/development institution or even a university. In this context, students are asked to:
- carry out personal and original work on a specific subject;
- show initiative and creativity;
- address and integrate various aspects of the subject as well as its environment;
- produce a synthesis of the related knowledge anddemonstrate the ability to apply it;
- integrate sustainable and ethical dimensions;
- think critically;
- justify their choices.
The educational support seminars aim to support students during the completion of their graduation work. Firstly, students will be supported in the choice of their subject of work, the writing of their research question, research objectives and research hypotheses, bibliographic research and realisation of the state of the art, the process of writing the thesis document and the preparation for the oral defense in front of the jury. Secondly, students will be trained to self-assessment, that is to say to carry out a reflective analysis of their own student path in terms of skills developed, identification of their own strengths and weaknesses, their wishes for future continuing education, with a view to their integration into the professional world of the health sector.
